count.influx:
from(bucket: "example_bucket")
  |> range(start: 0)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "example_measurement1")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._field == "field1")
  |> count()

integral.influx:
from(bucket: "example_bucket")
  |> range(start: 0)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "example_measurement1")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._field == "field1")
  |> integral()
integral.postgres: SELECT SUM((next_time - timestamp) * (field1 + next_field1) / 2) AS integral FROM (SELECT timestamp, field1, LEAD(timestamp) OVER (ORDER BY timestamp) AS next_time, LEAD(field1) OVER (ORDER BY timestamp) AS next_field1 FROM example_table1) t WHERE next_time IS NOT NULL;
